    "title": "Sarovar Hotels Capital India is Hiring: Guest Relations Manager (Senior)",
    "description": "Grow your career with Sarovar Hotels Capital India! We are hiring a Guest Relations Manager for our Gwalior team. Be part of a workplace that celebrates innovation, diversity, and performance.\n\nAbout Sarovar Hotels Capital India:\nSarovar Hotels Capital India is a leading organization in the Hybrid sector, committed to excellence, innovation, and employee growth. We offer a dynamic work environment where talent is recognized and rewarded.\n\nKey Responsibilities:\n• Plan and execute banquets, events, and MICE functions\n• Assist in menu planning, costing, and food festival coordination\n• Conduct regular guest satisfaction surveys and implement improvements\n• Manage front office operations including check-in/check-out\n• Manage reservations and optimize room revenue through yield management\n• Manage procurement of hotel supplies and control operating costs\n• Prepare daily operating reports and present to management\n\nRequired Skills & Qualifications:\n• BPharm / MPharm / PharmD\n• 0-1 years of relevant experience\n• Proficiency in Customer Relations\n• Proficiency in Revenue Management\n• Proficiency in HACCP\n• Proficiency in Hotel Management\n• Proficiency in Crisis Management\n• Proficiency in Tour Planning\n• Proficiency in GDS Systems\n• Proficiency in F&B Service\n\nWork Mode: Hybrid - Flexible work-from-home and office\n\nWhat We Offer:\n• Annual paid leaves and casual leaves\n• Employee stock options (ESOPs) for eligible roles\n• Work-from-home flexibility\n• Life and accident insurance\n• Comprehensive health insurance for self and family\n• Company-sponsored certifications\n• Salary Range: 2.5 LPA - 6 LPA per annum\n\nLocation: Gwalior, Madhya Pradesh, India\n\nIf you are excited about this opportunity, apply now and take the next step in your career journey with Sarovar Hotels Capital India!",
